  user_input {
    user_response: "Act as an Expert Frontend Developer and UI/UX Engineer. I am building the frontend for an IoT & Edge AI Capstone Project called \"SIPESAT (SIstem PEmilah SAmpah Terpadu)\". \n\nI have uploaded several reference files:\n1. A logo image to extract exact branding colors.\n2. `DESIGN.md`: The complete design system (Lumina Ecology) containing color hex codes, typography rules, and spacing.\n3. `code.html`: The base HTML structure, Tailwind CSS configuration, and sidebar navigation implementation.\n4. Four screenshots representing the exact 4 views I need: \n   - Authentication/Login View (\"Access Ecosystem\")\n   - User Dashboard View (Halo, Alex! with QR Code button & Balance)\n   - AI Evaluation View (Waste Distribution chart & Recommendations)\n   - Machine Status View (Real-time Bin Capacities)\n\nYOUR TASK:\nWrite a complete, fully functional React component (e.g., `App.jsx`) using Tailwind CSS that exactly replicates these 4 screens. Combine them into a single cohesive application.\n\nSTRICT REQUIREMENTS:\n1. Navigation & State: Implement a state variable (e.g., `currentView`) to toggle between the 4 views using the Sidebar Navigation. The sidebar must be persistent on the left (as shown in the `code.html` and screenshots).\n2. Styling & Tailwind: Use the exact color hex codes and tailwind configuration provided in `DESIGN.md` and `code.html`. Ensure the \"Glassmorphism\" effect (`backdrop-filter: blur()`), dark mode backgrounds, and neon glow effects are applied accurately.\n3. Branding Updates: Integrate the primary colors from the uploaded Logo (Green, Yellow, Blue) into the UI elements where appropriate, replacing the older cyan/purple accents, while keeping the overall dark aesthetic.\n4. Typography: Use the Google Fonts requested (`Geist` for headings/labels and `Inter` for body text).\n5. Pixel-Perfect Layouts: \n   - Replicate the exact structure of the Bento Grid in the Machine Status view.\n   - Replicate the exact layout of the User Dashboard (Balance card, QR button, 4 mini stats cards, Recent Transactions).\n   - Replicate the Login card structure precisely.\n6. Icons: Use Material Symbols Outlined (as configured in the `code.html`) or `lucide-react`.\n\nDo not omit any details. Please provide the complete React code, including the necessary imports and the Tailwind configuration object so I can run this locally in a Vite or Next.js environment immediately."
    items {
      text: "Act as an Expert Frontend Developer and UI/UX Engineer. I am building the frontend for an IoT & Edge AI Capstone Project called \"SIPESAT (SIstem PEmilah SAmpah Terpadu)\". \n\nI have uploaded several reference files:\n1. A logo image to extract exact branding colors.\n2. `DESIGN.md`: The complete design system (Lumina Ecology) containing color hex codes, typography rules, and spacing.\n3. `code.html`: The base HTML structure, Tailwind CSS configuration, and sidebar navigation implementation.\n4. Four screenshots representing the exact 4 views I need: \n   - Authentication/Login View (\"Access Ecosystem\")\n   - User Dashboard View (Halo, Alex! with QR Code button & Balance)\n   - AI Evaluation View (Waste Distribution chart & Recommendations)\n   - Machine Status View (Real-time Bin Capacities)\n\nYOUR TASK:\nWrite a complete, fully functional React component (e.g., `App.jsx`) using Tailwind CSS that exactly replicates these 4 screens. Combine them into a single cohesive application.\n\nSTRICT REQUIREMENTS:\n1. Navigation & State: Implement a state variable (e.g., `currentView`) to toggle between the 4 views using the Sidebar Navigation. The sidebar must be persistent on the left (as shown in the `code.html` and screenshots).\n2. Styling & Tailwind: Use the exact color hex codes and tailwind configuration provided in `DESIGN.md` and `code.html`. Ensure the \"Glassmorphism\" effect (`backdrop-filter: blur()`), dark mode backgrounds, and neon glow effects are applied accurately.\n3. Branding Updates: Integrate the primary colors from the uploaded Logo (Green, Yellow, Blue) into the UI elements where appropriate, replacing the older cyan/purple accents, while keeping the overall dark aesthetic.\n4. Typography: Use the Google Fonts requested (`Geist` for headings/labels and `Inter` for body text).\n5. Pixel-Perfect Layouts: \n   - Replicate the exact structure of the Bento Grid in the Machine Status view.\n   - Replicate the exact layout of the User Dashboard (Balance card, QR button, 4 mini stats cards, Recent Transactions).\n   - Replicate the Login card structure precisely.\n6. Icons: Use Material Symbols Outlined (as configured in the `code.html`) or `lucide-react`.\n\nDo not omit any details. Please provide the complete React code, including the necessary imports and the Tailwind configuration object so I can run this locally in a Vite or Next.js environment immediately."
    }
