the four dashboards. The sidebar\'s persistent visibility is confirmed, and I\'ve designed a responsive mobile navigation. I\'m focusing on the login/logout functionality: ensuring users see the Access Ecosystem first when logged out, and then are seamlessly directed to the dashboard upon login. The persistent navigation allows logging in/out from any view. This elegantly addresses both login structure and view toggling!\n\n\n**Refining Sidebar Functionality**\n\nI\'ve got the view toggling functioning through the sidebar. Users can now seamlessly navigate to Dashboard, Analytics, and Devices, plus initiate Log Out, which brings them to the login screen. Also, I\'ve confirmed persistent navigation, and I\'ve designed a responsive mobile navigation. I\'m focusing on the login/logout functionality: ensuring users see the Access Ecosystem first when logged out, and then are seamlessly directed to the dashboard upon login. The persistent navigation allows logging in/out from any view. This elegantly addresses both login structure and view toggling!\n\nNow, I\'m verifying the font imports and styling configurations to ensure everything works together properly. I\'m currently designing the final `/src/index.css` file to handle these imports and accurately configure the Tailwind v4 theme, incorporating the custom colors. Tailwind CSS v4\'s theme directive will configure custom colors with `@theme`. I\'ve started the definition of colors such as `--color-background`, `--color-surface-container-lowest`, `--color-surface-container-low`, `--color-surface-container`, `--color-surface-container-high`, `--color-surface-container-highest`, `--color-surface`, `--color-on-surface`, `--color-on-surface-variant`, `--color-primary-fixed-dim`.\n\n\n**Refining Theme & Styling**\n\nI\'ve clarified the Tailwind v4 theme usage with `@theme`, ensuring clean CSS variable definitions for colors, fonts, and utilities. I\'ll craft the custom styles, including glass pane, floating orbs, and neon glowing shadows, directly within `src/index.css`. I\'ve realized that I must install `recharts` to enable charts, or alternatively, I could design SVG-based custom charts.\n\n\n**Prioritizing SVG Chart Design**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing the implementation of a custom SVG-based donut chart. Given the React 19 environment and potential `recharts` compatibility issues, I realize a custom solution is both safer and more precise. SVG charts offer pixel-perfect rendering, interactive features, and eliminate dependency errors, ensuring immediate reliability. Plus, I can tailor beautiful glowing drop shadows and slice highlights.\n\n\n**Designing SVG & Types**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in designing a stunning, interactive SVG pie chart, complete with hover tooltips, click events, and pixel-perfect styling. With my React 19 environment, this custom approach is ensuring error-free compilation and a high-end display. I\'m also creating a types file, `/src/types.ts`, for data structures, transactions, and state representations. I\'m proceeding to develop detailed components for each of the four views.\n\n\n**Defining Dashboard Content**\n\nOkay, I\'m now outlining the dashboard views, starting with \"Halo, Alex! Dashboard View\". I\'ve created the structure using sidebar navigation. I\'m focusing on the \"Quick Stats\" cards, and I\'m integrating the provided data: 12 Batteries (active), 8 ATKs (active), 15 Box Packaging (active), and 24 Small Bottles (active). I\'ll also design each dashboard view\'s required content, per the provided prompts and screenshots.\n\n\n**Constructing Dashboard Views**\n\nNow, I\'m developing the \"Dashboard View.\" I\'m implementing the top app bar with notification and user profile, and crafting the \"Halo, Alex! \360\237\221\213\" welcome header. I\'m building the \"Saldo Terkumpul\" balance card and the four mini-stat cards with hover effects and icons for batteries, ATK, packaging, and bottles. The recent transactions list is up next, along with the responsive mobile bottom navigation.\n\n\n**Visualizing Dashboard Content**\n\nI\'m now fully focused on the visual design and content integration for each dashboard view. I\'m building out the SVG donut chart with interactive hover states and clear legends, incorporating the specified percentages for \"Kotak\" and \"Botol\".  I\'m also crafting the AI recommendation card, and the system node status cards, and the simulated \"clean wave graphs\" for recycling rates, CO2 offset, and energy saved.\n\n\n"
