  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Examining Component Structure**\n\nI\'ve successfully created several helper components, including Sidebar, TopBar, LoginView, DashboardView, AnalyticsView, and DevicesView. Now, I need to analyze the project\'s overall structure and ensure these are properly integrated and that I haven\'t overlooked any necessary files or updates, specifically, `/src/App.tsx`.\n\n\n**Crafting Complete Layout**\n\nOkay, I\'m now drafting a full layout for `/src/App.tsx`. I\'ll retain the existing state variables. The `isAuthenticated` variable will be initialized to `true` to immediately showcase the app\'s capabilities, but also allow them to log out to experience the `LoginView`. Once authentication is complete, clicking login will set `isAuthenticated` to true. This method satisfies the requirement of immediate accessibility and displaying the login view through logging out.\n\n\n**Defining State Properties**\n\nI\'m now detailing the application\'s core state properties, focusing on user interaction and data representation. I\'ll include `currentView`, set to \'dashboard\' by default, and `currentPersona`, set to \'Alex\', encompassing user roles and profile information. I\'ll initialize a `balance` and `transactions` array, pre-populated with example data. I also have an initial `binCapacities` object with default capacities and color-coded statuses. I\'m considering a simulator action involving battery deposits, which will increment counts, update percentages, and append transactions.\n\n\n**Simulating Real Interactions**\n\nI\'m working on interactive elements now. Depositing a bottle increases counts, updates percentages, and appends a transaction, reflecting a dynamic database. This simulation provides core functionality that mirrors physical sorting nodes. It\'s fully interactive and engaging. I\'ve also confirmed the bottom navigation bar for mobile navigation, enhancing the user experience.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now update `/src/App.tsx` to serve as the cohesive core coordinator of the SIPESAT system. It manages state variables for real-time sensor updates, deposit verification, transaction lists, user session metrics, and routes between views using sidebar/bottom nav toggles."
