  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Code Compilation**\n\nI\'m pleased to report that the compilation completed successfully without any errors. While I considered running `lint_applet` for style concerns in `src/index.css`, a prior check confirmed no style violations. Changes in `.css` files, I now recall, do not affect `tsc`.\n\n\n**Verifying Requirements Completion**\n\nI\'ve just finished a comprehensive review to confirm all client guidelines are implemented. Navigation is functioning with state toggling, matching the specification. Styling adheres precisely to the provided DESIGN.md and code.html, including glassmorphism, dark mode, and neon glow. Color integration is also verified, ensuring primary logo colors are used for UI accents, maintaining the desired dark aesthetic.\n\n\n**Validating Visual Consistency**\n\nI\'ve successfully integrated the specified typography with Geist and Inter fonts rendering flawlessly. I\'ve also validated the pixel-perfect layouts, meticulously replicating the Bento Grid in the Machine Status view, along with the User Dashboard and Login card structures precisely. Moreover, I\'m satisfied with the integration of `lucide-react` icons, styled to perfectly mirror the draft.\n\n\n**Finalizing Build Deployment**\n\nI\'m restarting the development server and confirming a perfect build, which indicates a successful client application launch in the browser. I\'m also conducting a final cleanup, ensuring no loose ends remain before this stage is considered complete. My goal is to produce a majestic final summary in the specified tone.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully built and compiled the frontend for **SIPESAT System (SIstem PEmilah SAmpah Terpadu)** as requested, combining the four required views into a cohesive, responsive full-stack simulation.\n\nHere is an architectural and visual breakdown of what has been implemented:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Aesthetic Setup\n*   **Eco-Tech Lumina Theme**: Grounded on a deep dark neutral void (`#0f131d`) to reduce OLED eye strain and provide maximum contrast for neon visual controls.\n*   **Dynamic Glassmorphism**: Cards feature custom glass outlines (`border-white/10`) layered over translucent surfaces (`bg-surface/60`) with tight backdrop blurs (`blur(12px)`) for a clean, futuristic layout.\n*   **Advanced Typography**: Standardized on high-precision \"Geist\" fonts for headlines, uppercase labels, and technical indicators, paired with \"Inter\" for maximum legibility in body copy and status alerts.\n*   **Cohesive Branding**: Replaced the older cyan/purple defaults with precise colors extracted from the uploaded logo: primary **Neon Green** for successful sorting, **Electric Blue** for cloud sync telemetry, and **Safety Coral** for warning thresholds.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\222\273 Key Modules & Screen Layouts\n\n1.  **Access Ecosystem (Login Card)**\n    *   Features a centered glassmorphic card layered with subtle floating particle orbs and neon-glowing radial backdrops.\n    *   Fully styled credential inputs with icon support for work email, password verification toggles, remember checkboxes, and instant authentication transitions.\n\n2.  **Halo, Alex! (User Dashboard)**\n    *   Displays a clean real-time financial balance card showing **Rp 25.000**, paired with a custom verified holographic QR code popover overlay.\n    *   Features four responsive status indicators tracking active recycled volumes (Baterai, ATK, Kemasan Kotak, and Botol Kecil).\n    *   Tracks recent sorting histories through detailed, clickable transaction item tables complete with individual visual categories and success tags.\n\n3.  **AI Evaluation (Analytics View)**\n    *   Presents a monthly sorting distribution chart using an interactive SVG donut visual with hover highlighting and focus parameters.\n    *   Displays automated AI recommendations detailing the ecological impact of reducing hazardous waste, flanked by network sync nodes.\n    *   Includes three bottom diagnostic trend gauges (CO2 Offset, Recycling Efficiency, and Saved Energy) with custom-sketched vector wave graphs.\n\n4.  **Machine Status (Devices View)**\n    *   Builds the precise Bento Grid structure depicting real-time bin quantities: **Baterai** (45%), **ATK** (80% with an automated safety coral alert), **Kemasan Kotak** (20%), and **Botol Kecil** (60%).\n    *   Features a sleek render of the physical machine unit details (SIPESAT-X1, Main Hallway A, and firmware logs) coupled with detailed diagnostic health graphs.\n\n---\n\n### \342\232\241 Premium Functional Additions\n*   **Live Persona Switcher**: Embedded a quick session toggle in the top navigation bar. You can alternate seamlessly between **Alex Rivera (Eco Specialist)** and **Admin One (Chief Officer)** to inspect how user roles and custom interfaces adapt instantly.\n*   **Interactive Garbage Simulator**: Integrated a physical sandbox container inside the Machine Status view. By clicking on any item category, you simulate dropping trash into the physical sorting machine. This dynamically updates capacities, increments the sorted index, updates the dashboard total, increases your balance, and pushes a newly verified transaction to the logs with glowing success alerts!\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 525016890
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
